<subSubSection id="C329A9DA2A5E9716FF7AFAB85A5CA002" pageId="7" pageNumber="181" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8CFA512A5E9716FF7AFAB85A5CA002" blockId="7.[151,1436,1351,1664]" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="B94726432A5E9716FF7AFAB8596EA33F" bold="true" box="[151,256,1351,1376]" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">Remark.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3381D22A5E9716FE48FAB75A5DA33F" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[421,563,1352,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terlineata">
<emphasis id="B94726432A5E9716FE48FAB75A5DA33F" box="[421,563,1352,1376]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">S. terlineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unknown. Nevertheless, according to the female genitalia structure (the sclerotized ductus bursae (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3381D22A5E9716FE32FA935A2DA3DB" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[479,579,1388,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94726432A5E9716FE32FA935A2DA3DB" box="[479,579,1388,1412]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">Afrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ductus bursae is subdivided into antrum and membranous anterior part), the presence of the postero-lateral sclerotized area in the corpus bursae, the presence of the lateral band-like signum, and the elongate and twisted appendix bursae) and the forewing coloration and pattern, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3381D22A5E9716FB8EFA4B5CBEA393" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[1123,1232,1460,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terlineata">
<emphasis id="B94726432A5E9716FB8EFA4B5CBEA393" box="[1123,1232,1460,1484]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">terlineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C3381D22A5E9716FEE4FA275923A3B0" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1854" box="[265,333,1496,1519]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Siccia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94726432A5E9716FEE4FA275923A3B0" box="[265,333,1496,1519]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">Siccia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3381D22A5E9716FD89FA275BB2A3AF" authority="Hampson, 1914" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1914" box="[612,988,1496,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Siccia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conformis">
<emphasis id="B94726432A5E9716FD89FA275B71A3AF" box="[612,799,1496,1520]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">Siccia conformis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA287A02A5E9716FCCBFA275BB2A3AF" author="Hampson, G. F." box="[806,988,1496,1520]" pageId="7" pageNumber="181" refId="ref3881" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1914) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum. Supplement. Uol. 1. Trustees of the British Museum, London, XXVIII + 858 pp." type="book" year="1914">Hampson, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The genitalia of the female 
<typeStatus id="548844F32A5E9716FAF6FA285D13A3AF" box="[1307,1405,1495,1520]" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3381D22A5E9716FF7AFA03594FA04B" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[151,289,1532,1556]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terlineata">
<emphasis id="B94726432A5E9716FF7AFA03594FA04B" box="[151,289,1532,1556]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">S. terlineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1308E6D42A5E9716FEDCFA0359EDA04A" box="[305,387,1532,1557]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[209,1436,183,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,177,1916]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 15–17. Afrasura spp.: male genitalia. 15, A. pallescens, Togo, slide AV5092 Volynkin; 16, A. pallescens, Zambia, slide AV5096 Volynkin; 17, A. hieroglyphica, Sierra Leone, slide AV4504 Volynkin." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2944151/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) differs only slightly from that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3381D22A5E9716FCE7FA035BF9A04B" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1914" box="[778,919,1532,1556]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Siccia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conformis">
<emphasis id="B94726432A5E9716FCE7FA035BF9A04B" box="[778,919,1532,1556]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">S. conformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1308E6D42A5E9716FC4AFA035B95A04A" box="[935,1019,1532,1557]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[209,1436,183,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,177,1916]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 15–17. Afrasura spp.: male genitalia. 15, A. pallescens, Togo, slide AV5092 Volynkin; 16, A. pallescens, Zambia, slide AV5096 Volynkin; 17, A. hieroglyphica, Sierra Leone, slide AV4504 Volynkin." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2944151/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
), rendering this taxon presumably to be just a synonym of the widespread and polymorphic 
<taxonomicName id="4C3381D22A5E9716FCD4F9DF5BA2A067" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1914" box="[825,972,1568,1592]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Siccia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conformis">
<emphasis id="B94726432A5E9716FCD4F9DF5BA2A067" box="[825,972,1568,1592]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">S. conformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. To clarify the status of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3381D22A5E9716FAE8F9DF5DFBA067" authorityName="Durante" authorityYear="2009" box="[1285,1429,1568,1592]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terlineata">
<emphasis id="B94726432A5E9716FAE8F9DF5DFBA067" box="[1285,1429,1568,1592]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">S. terlineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, examination of its male is necessary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C329A9DA2A5E9716FF2AF9985D7CA0DF" box="[199,1298,1639,1664]" pageId="7" pageNumber="181" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8CFA512A5E9716FF2AF9985D7CA0DF" blockId="7.[151,1436,1351,1664]" box="[199,1298,1639,1664]" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="B94726432A5E9716FF2AF998590EA0DF" bold="true" box="[199,352,1639,1664]" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species is known from its 
<typeStatus id="548844F32A5E9716FD50F9975A83A0DF" box="[701,749,1640,1664]" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">type</typeStatus>
locality only, Lake Langano in Central 
<collectingCountry id="F324BAC12A5E9716FB41F9985D61A0DF" box="[1196,1295,1639,1664]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="7" pageNumber="181">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
